               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400106-name-549" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400106-name-549" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400106-name-549" type="surname" value="MARGESUM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400106-name-549" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MARGESUM.</persName>
                  </hi>I am assistant to Samuel James Nichols, linen<lb></lb>draper, Chiswell-street. On the evening of the 2nd of January, at half<lb></lb>past five o'clock, I was behind the counter, and observed a cloak go off the line in the shop—I jumped over the counter, ran out, and saw the prisoner outside tucking the cloak under his coat—I pursued him to Finsbury<lb></lb>square, and stopped him—he dropped the cloak—I took it up, still followed,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184001060079"></xptr>
               <p>and took him—I lost sight of him for a moment, while he turned the corner of Wilson-street—when I turned, he was in custody—he had a leather cap and apron on when I first saw him, but he dropped the cap in running, and tried to get the apron off, but I am sure he is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q</hi>. Did you see me with the cloak? <hi rend="italic">A</hi>. Yes, it was about half-past five o'clock, it was quite light enough to see you.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400106-name-550" type="witnessName">
